Which option within a systemd timer unit file is used to specify when a job should run?
A)  OnCalendar=
B)  Time=
C)  RunAt=
D)  TimedEvent=
A
A. The OnCalendar= configuration option is used to set the time when an event will runwhen using systemd timer unit files. The other options shown are not valid for use withsystemd timer files.
